OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F439A1773666674
OL,3,CHusband said he would 'cut up and
OL,4,Cdissolve wife's body', court hears
OL,6,FMrs Baird said Trybus stayed in her
OL,7,Fhome for six months after her
OL,8,Fdaughter's death. She said Trybus
OL,9,Fwould always wear his wedding ring,
OL,10,Fbut two weeks after her death he
OL,11,Fstopped wearing it and she found it on
OL,12,Fhis bedside table.
OL,14,FTrybus denies the charges and the
OL,15,Ftrial continues.
